		<div id="categorycontent">
			<h3>Development</h3>
			<blockquote>
				CitrusDB is developed under the <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html">GPL version 2</a> license.  This project was started by Paul Yasi (paul at citrusdb.org), originally to fulfill his own customer database needs.  It is developed by a small group of coders from around the world.
				<p>
				Do you want to contribute source code?  Please read the <a href="coding.html">coding standards</a> and join the <a href="https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/citrusdb-devel">development mailing list</a> to post your ideas to get started.
			<p>
			Translations are also needed, you can help by updating the translations included with the release or contribute new translation files.  Please email them to: paul at citrusdb.org.
			<p>
			Documentation can also be improved.  All comments and contributions to the documentation can be sent to paul at citrusdb.org.
			<p>
			Bug reports and fixes are welcome.  You can look through the list of bugs in the <a href="http://bugs.citrusdb.org/view_all_bug_page.php">Bug Tracking</a> page.  If you have found a new bug, please <a href="http://bugs.citrusdb.org/bug_report_page.php">report it</a>.  It would be helpful to sign up for a new account in the bug tracker first so you can be notified of changes to the status of your bug.
			</blockquote>
